args: Hmm? What are you doing, Melody?
I just finished hanging up the laundry.
Melody? Where is the laundry I asked\nyou to take care of?
The laundry? I just finished hanging it\nall...up...to...dry?
AAAAAH! THE WIND IS BLOWING IT AWAY!
...Melody? I want you to listen to me\nvery closely.

That was several days' worth of clothes.
If you don't get them back, we're all going
to be wandering around naked tomorrow.
...Even Ranzal.
Eeep! I'm so sorry! I'll go find them\nright now!
She really seems to be trying her best.\nLet's give it a bit more time.
Well, I suppose she's a hard worker\nin...some respects.
And no matter how angry I get, \nshe never lets it get her down.
Surely you MUST agree with me now.\nWe hired her thinking she would decrease\nmy workload, but she's done the opposite.
Here's an idea: Why don't you give her\na test of some kind?
Give her a task. Something basic.\nIf she can do it, she stays.
It can't make that much extra work for you\nif it's something simple, right?
I feel like this is going to finish her off,\nbut...very well.
Anything to stop her from interfering\nwith the laundry again.
...You want me to make a cup of tea that\nsatisfies Prince {player_name}?
That's right. If you can do that,\nI won't fire you.
Really?! Th-then I'll do my best!
Okay! First I need to light the stove and\nboil some water. That means I need\nmatches, whiiich...aaaare...riiiight...
You might want to pay a little more\nattention while you're searching.
The container with all the tea leaves has\ngot caught on your sleev— Oh dear.
Oh my gosh, I am SO sorry, Cleo.\nI'll just get another bag of tea leaves.
Melody, that bag contains flour.\nThe tea leaves are over—
*cough* *hack* *wheeze* D-don't worry!\nI'll clean this up right away...
STOP! Don't...touch...anything. I'll do it.\nYou just focus on making the tea.
Right! Okay, Melody, you can do this.\nFirst, I need to light the stove...
How is this even possible?!\nAll I wanted to do was make tea!
I have the exact same question.
...We HAVE to get rid of this woman,\n{player_name}.
I hear what you're saying, but I also think\nyou may be overlooking her strong points.
No matter how many times you get angry\nwith her, she always stays positive and\ncheerful, right?
Everyone tends to get a bit gloomy after\nwe've been fighting for a while, so I think\nsuch cheer is important for morale.
Even if her housekeeping abilities are...\na little lacking.
She lacks housekeeping skills in the same\nway I lack a second head.
...But this is your castle. If you want me to\ngive her more time, I will do so.
*sniff* You're both so good to me...
This time, I won't let you down!
